NEW ORLEANS A southern
white woman, Mrs. Virginia Cox,
continues to demonstrate her be-
lief in an integrated society.


She won suit which gave her
the right to attend Southern Uni
versity, Negro school.


She lives in a predominantly
Negro suburb and teaches at
Catholic high school for Negro
boys.


Mrs. Cox is seeking election
next month on the Orleans Parish
school board.


She comments that there are
about 800 Negroes attending in
tegrated schools. There are
$3.50 Negroes in school, but
only $4,000 whites. However,
the Negro schools are over
crowded.
